<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>By default, OpenGL writes scene depth information into the depth buffer in the range [0.0, 1.0] with 0.0 corresponding to the near clip plane and 1.0 to the far clip plane. <db:link xlink:href="qt3drender-qdepthrange.xml">QDepthRange</db:link> allows mapping these values into a different range so parts of the scene are always rendered in front of or behind other parts. Valid values for near and far are between 0 and 1.</db:para>
</db:section>
